16 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
17 This measure amends Section 3 of Article 7-B of the Oklahoma
18 Constitution. It changes provisions related to the Judicial
19 Nominating Commission. It updates references so that
20 appointments made by certain persons based on the congressional
21 districts would be made using the current congressional
22 districts instead of the districts as they were constituted when
23 this section of the Constitution was originally adopted in 1967.
24 It removes a prohibition on certain members of the Commission so
Req. No. 1826 Page 5

1 that the member could be a licensed attorney. It allows a
2 person to serve on the Commission even if he or she is related
3 to a licensed attorney. It changes the terms so that each term
4 would be for six (6) years. It removes restrictions based on
5 political party membership. It removes a provision that
6 prohibits a member of the Commission from succeeding himself or
7 herself on the Commission.
